Collecting circumstances.
This species appears to inhabit isolated, clean water bodies. The specimens were collected in a side pool of a stream (
Fig. 40
), an ephemeral puddle with decaying leaves (
Fig. 41
) and muddy substrate, in remnant pools with pebbles as substrate formed in drying streams (
Fig. 39
); also in nearly permanent man-made tanks and small puddles (
Fig. 42
) on basaltic rocks. The physicochemical parameters of water bodies range as follows: pH: 6.2 to 9.0, temperature 18 to 25 0C and salinity 23 to 115 ppm.
